.TH AGENT-HOOK-PRE-MCP 1 "2026-06-30" "agentguard" "User Commands"
.SH NAME
agent-hook-pre-mcp \- guard agent MCP tool calls before execution
.SH SYNOPSIS
.B agent-hook-pre-mcp
.SH DESCRIPTION
.B agent-hook-pre-mcp
reads an MCP hook JSON payload from standard input. It blocks MCP servers after
repeated failures, warns on expensive or under-scoped MCP calls, and then lets
local extensions add environment-specific MCP policy.
.PP
The base policy warns on exact
.B search_files
leaf-tool calls without a path filter and warns once on exact
.B knowledge_load
leaf-tool calls because large documents can consume significant context.
.SH EXIT STATUS
.TP
.B 0
The MCP call is allowed, possibly with warnings.
.TP
.B 2
The MCP call is blocked.
.SH SEE ALSO
.BR agent-hook-post-mcp (1)
